# NOTE: `package.json#files` is the source of truth for what gets published.
# It is an allowlist ("src/**/*", "tsconfig.json", "README.md", ".env.example"),
# and it wins over this file. This list only documents intent and guards against
# an accidental addition; it must never exclude anything `files` ships.
#
# This package publishes its **TypeScript source** and runs on Bun — there is no
# compiled bundle. Do NOT re-add `src/`, `tsconfig.json` or `*.ts` here: they are
# the only runnable entrypoint.

# Development files
tests/
scripts/
docs/
reviews/
qa/
coverage/

# Local environment — the example is published, real secrets are not
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Tooling config (not needed by consumers)
biome.json
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# IDE and OS files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Git / CI
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# Dependency directories
node_modules/

# Output of 'npm pack'
*.tgz

# Claude and development specific files
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
claude-swarm.*
ruv-swarm*

# Misc
*.bak
*.tmp
.codegraph/
